OL,6,F2022 has been the worst year for real
OL,7,Fwage growth in nearly half a century, a
OL,8,Fstudy says.
OL,10,FWages have fallen by 3 per cent, after
OL,11,Fthe cost of living is been taken into
OL,12,Faccount, making it the biggest drop
OL,13,Fsince 1977 and the second worst on
OL,14,Frecord since 1945, according to the
OL,15,FTrades Union Congress (TUC).
OL,17,FIt said workers have lost #76 a month
OL,18,Fon average this year as a result of
OL,19,Ftheir pay not keeping pace with
OL,20,Finflation, with those in the public
OL,21,Fsector losing #180.
